    ) VALUES (1396195, 'Clozapine', 'Ritonavir', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration with ritonavir may theoretically increase the serum concentrations of clozapine. The proposed mechanism is ritonavir inhibition of clozapine metabolism via CYP450 3A4 and 2D6. Clozapine is also metabolized by CYP450 1A2. Because it is a substrate for several different CYP450 enzymes, the risk of metabolic interactions caused by an effect on an individual isoform is thought to be minimized.', NULL, 'Caution is advised if clozapine is prescribed in combination with ritonavir.', NULL, 'Caution is advised if clozapine is prescribed in combination with ritonavir. Pharmacologic response to clozapine should be monitored more closely whenever ritonavir is added to or withdrawn from therapy in patients stabilized on their existing antipsychotic regimen, and the clozapine dosage adjusted as necessary.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317475);
